This paper deals with natural language understanding (NLU) models and their biases, which are common topics in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on large-scale datasets, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) if the datasets involve sensitive information.
